HEADWORD: Boltonite
<hw>Bol"ton*ite</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Min.)</fld>
<def>A granular mineral of a grayish or yellowish color, found in
Bolton, Massachusetts. It is a silicate of magnesium, belonging to the
chrysolite family.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

